Symantec: Results
MITRE Engenuity does not assign scores, rankings, or ratings. The evaluation results are available to the public, so other organizations may provide their own analysis and interpretation - these are not endorsed or validated by MITRE.

Alerting Strategy

Events that are deemed to be related to a compromise are assigned appropriate severity values (Low, Medium, High). These compromise-related events are also enriched with contextual information, such as a short description or potential mappings to related ATT&CK Tactics and Techniques. Events potentially associated with compromise are aggregated into specific views and tagged with corresponding IOCs related to each event.

Correlation Strategy

Events are aggregated into a central queue, where the data for each can be explored. Data within each event captures relevant evidence, including correlation between surrounding system events such as process lineage or interactions between processes and files. There are additional dashboards that provide a wider perspective on events across multiple hosts. There is also the ability to correlate events across more in-depth data captured from a full system dump.
